DURBAN - Police have arrested two men in connection with the murder of a Doonside businessman.&nbsp; Last week the shopowner was killed during a robbery at his store, situated on Main Road. Russel Meiring, ER24 spokesman, said when emergency teams arrived, they found the businessowner lying motionless on the ground.&nbsp;&quot;The man was assessed by ER24 paramedics and found to have sustained a fatal gunshot wound to his chest and showed no signs of life. Unfortunately, nothing could be done for the man and he was declared dead on the scene,&quot; he said.&nbsp;On Wednesday at around 3am, a joint operation led to the arrests of two men in Wentworth.&nbsp;A source close to the investigation, revealed that police followed up on information received and made their way to two properties where they made the arrests.&nbsp;Police found the car that the two men had allegedly used and personal items belonging to the victim including his driver's license.&nbsp;The car was allegedly stolen in Gauteng and had false number plates. Two more men, believed to be involved in the murder, are still on the run.&nbsp; Daily News